# Fargate tasks (backend and frontend) require HTTPS egress to 0.0.0.0/0 so
# they can reach AWS APIs (ECR image pull, Secrets Manager, CloudWatch Logs)
# via the NAT gateway in the public subnet. The alternative — VPC interface
# endpoints for each service — costs ~$7/month per endpoint and is deferred.
# All other egress rules have been scoped to specific ports and the VPC CIDR.
AVD-AWS-0104

# ALB listeners use HTTP (port 80 production, port 8080 CodeDeploy test listener).
# HTTPS termination via ACM + Route 53 is a planned addition; HTTP is acceptable
# while the domain and certificate are not yet provisioned.
# Suppressed as CKV_AWS_2 in .checkov.yaml for the same reason.
AVD-AWS-0054

# The ALB is intentionally public-facing — it serves end-user traffic from the
# internet. Setting internal=false is correct and expected for this workload.
AVD-AWS-0053

# nginx must run as root to bind to port 80 — the master process needs the
# privileged port, and worker processes already drop to the nginx user
# internally. Switching to an unprivileged port (8080) would require updating
# the ALB target groups, security groups, and task definitions throughout the
# stack; deferred until a rootless nginx migration is planned.
DS-0002 frontend/Dockerfile

# SNS topic is encrypted with the AWS-managed key (alias/aws/sns).
# A customer-managed KMS key (CMK) would satisfy this check but costs $1/month
# per key; acceptable risk for non-production alert topics, deferred for prod.
AVD-AWS-0136
